text: Staff was very rude and didn't speak to me nicely. Wasn't helpful at all. Didn't answer my question. I asked nicely and she replied with an annoyed tone.

The outlet has long queues and the queue moves slowly due to staff ignoring the queue. All seems to be engrossed in doing their work despite multiple "hello", "hi" and "excuse me". Perhaps they are waiting for one another to attend to the long queue.

There seems to be additional fee when paying using Changi Pay. You will need to pay S$6.60 for the S$6.50 every day value meal.

Worst Experience service was ok but in my drink their is something when i opened the cover there is something inside the drink i don't know what was that but it is his duty to check the glass properly and than served maybe the pickles are also spoiled because it taste bitter please served properlyüôèüèª.

How on earth does Singapore not have any gluten free options? This Subway, which notes it has gluten free, has no wrap or bread options and only a salad. When the majority of said salad is lettuce, 2 slices of tomato, and not much else, not sure what is on offer. Modernisation might be in order.
